The paper deals with managing large corpora of XML documents in large-scale P2P networks, which involves distributed storage and retrieval of data. This makes it likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Databases (cs.DB), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the efficient processing of queries, which falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of P2P networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the Peer-to-Peer (cs.P2P) sub-category.
